{{Top|canon=Petition of 2,000}}
{{Quote|This is a list of traitors!|[[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] discrediting the Petition of 2000's signers|<ref name="Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith (novelization)">[[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith (novelization)|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'' novelization]]</ref>}}
The '''Petition of 2000''' was a document drafted near the end of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] by a group of [[Senator/Legends|senators]] and other [[Politics/Legends|political]] officials (the "[[Delegation of 2000]]") addressed to [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. As Palpatine established the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]] and consolidated more and more power, some Republic senators watched with ever-growing concern. When they introduced measures or promoted actions to slow Palpatine's methodical power grab, they were stymied by the Chancellor's skillful use of bureaucracy and manipulation of public opinion.<ref name=":0" />

The Petition stated that, since the war's end was nearing, Palpatine should give up the emergency powers he had assumed since the end of the [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|Separatist Crisis]], which [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] realized would never happen under this Chancellor. It also specifically denounced the resurrected office of [[Moff/Legends|Moff]], as it would make the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Senate]] essentially powerless.

After the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic's]] transformation into the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], many senators removed their signatures from the petition. Nevertheless, all 2,000 were investigated by the newly created Imperial [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|intelligence]] agencies, including the [[Imperial Security Bureau/Legends|Imperial Security Bureau]]. Some were publicly cleared, while others were arrested; some disappeared forever.<ref name=":0">[[Star Wars: Age of Rebellion Core Rulebook|''Star Wars: Age of Rebellion'' Core Rulebook]]</ref>

